TY  - CONF
TI  - Port AGV Scheduling Based on Improved Aquila Optimizer Algorithm
AU  - Z. Zhang
AU  - F. Nie
AU  - W. Yang
AU  - Y. Nie
T2  - 2025 IEEE 8th International Electrical and Energy Conference (CIEEC)
AB  - In order to improve the efficiency of automated container terminals, it is crucial to optimize the scheduling of automated guided vehicles (AGV). Traditional AGV strategies tend to ignore the problems of running empty and carrying full weight. A method of Skyhawk optimization algorithm with penalty function is proposed. Weight constraints and time windows are integrated into the scheduling model, a constrained penalty strategy is used to handle the overweight container task, and a time window is utilized to define the loading and unloading sequence of each container, taking into account the vessel berthing time and the terminal's operational requirements. The problem of minimizing the no-load operation of AGV while reducing the full-load problem is achieved by using the Aquila Optimizer(AO) algorithm with a penalty function to obtain the minimum running time of the AGV. Simulation experiments are carried out with simulated data, and the experimental results provide optimal scheduling sequences for AGV, and the Aquila Optimizer algorithm shows some advantages among other algorithms.
C3  - 2025 IEEE 8th International Electrical and Energy Conference (CIEEC)
