TI  - Research on a UE5-Based Simulation System for Unmanned Surface Vessels in Complex Sea Conditions
AU  - C. Wang
AU  - J. Zheng
AU  - Y. Huang
AU  - Y. Zhao
T2  - 2025 IEEE International Conference on Unmanned Systems (ICUS)
AB  - A simulation system for unmanned surface vehicles (USVs) based on Unreal Engine 5 (UE5) is proposed and implemented in this paper. The system is designed to generate dynamic virtual environments simulating realistic ocean conditions with adjustable sea state levels. The deep integration of USV dynamics models with advanced virtual simulation capabilities of UE5 — including high-precision rendering, physics engine, and visual scripting — has enabled multidimensional technical coordination. The core objective of this research is the development of a human-machine interaction paradigm that combines virtual and physical elements, allowing users to control USVs in real-time while simultaneously monitoring operational status. This simulation platform is designed to provide an efficient and secure virtual experimental environment for USV mission planning, algorithm validation, and operational training under complex marine conditions, thereby enhancing safety and efficiency in real-world maritime operations.
